This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of Quicksort, which is a well-known sorting algorithm and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the number of comparisons made during the sorting process, which is a key aspect of algorithm analysis and falls under the category of algorithm analysis and complexity theory (cs.AL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of mathematical tools such as logarithms and harmonic numbers, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the performance of Quicksort on inputs with many duplicates, which is a topic related to parallel and distributed computing (cs.CC).
